WEBVTT

00:00:28.900 --> 00:00:30.221
now it's a communication.

00:00:30.245 --> 00:00:33.053
Everything that we choose
to put on is a narrative,

00:00:33.077 --> 00:00:35.098
a story about where we've been,

00:00:35.122 --> 00:00:36.714
what we're doing,

00:00:36.738 --> 00:00:37.938
who we want to be.

00:00:39.048 --> 00:00:40.796
I was a lonely kid.

00:00:40.820 --> 00:00:43.652
I didn't have an easy time
finding friends to play with,

00:00:43.676 --> 00:00:46.071
and I ended up making
a lot of my own play.

00:00:46.423 --> 00:00:48.902
I made a lot of my own toys.

00:00:48.926 --> 00:00:50.565
It began with ice cream.

00:00:50.589 --> 00:00:53.713
There was a Baskin-Robbins in my hometown,

00:00:53.737 --> 00:00:56.089
and they served ice cream
from behind the counter

00:00:56.113 --> 00:00:58.720
in these giant, five-gallon,
cardboard tubs.

00:00:58.744 --> 00:01:01.006
And someone told me --
I was eight years old --